  "notes": "The published Emscripten binary minifies its exports. In the JavaScript glue, `f` is memory, `g` is `__wasm_call_ctors`, `h` is `ZSTD_isError`, `i` is `ZSTD_compressBound`, `j`/`k` create/free compression contexts, `l` is `ZSTD_compress_usingDict`, `m` is `ZSTD_compress`, `n`/`o` create/free decompression contexts, `p` is `ZSTD_getFrameContentSize`, `q` is `ZSTD_decompress_usingDict`, `r` is `ZSTD_decompress`, and `s`/`t` are malloc/free. Tests drive raw exports directly, including normal compression, dictionary compression, decompression, and an error-classification path."
}
